  "prompt": "What is the best web prototyping/mockup tool?",
  "response": "The best web prototyping or mockup tool often depends on specific needs, team dynamics, and project requirements. Here are some of the most popular and highly regarded tools as of 2023:\n\n1. **Figma**: A collaborative web design tool that allows multiple users to work on the same project in real-time. It's great for both UI/UX design and prototyping.\n\n2. **Adobe XD**: Part of the Adobe Creative Cloud, XD offers robust features for wireframing, prototyping, and collaborating. It integrates well with other Adobe tools.\n\n3. **Sketch**: A vector-based design tool that's very popular among UI/UX designers, especially for macOS users. Its extensive plugins make it versatile for prototyping.\n\n4. **InVision**: Known for its prototyping capabilities, InVision allows designers to create interactive mockups and gather feedback from stakeholders. It integrates well with other design tools.\n\n5. **Axure RP**: A powerful tool for creating complex wireframes and interactive prototypes. It\u2019s particularly useful for projects requiring detailed specifications and user flows.\n\n6. **Balsamiq**: Ideal for low-fidelity wireframing, Balsamiq offers a simple interface that allows quick sketching of layout ideas without focusing on aesthetics.\n\n7. **Mockplus**: A user-friendly tool that supports rapid prototyping with a drag-and-drop interface. It's suitable for teams looking for a quick way to create interactive prototypes.\n\n8. **Framer**: Known for high-fidelity prototypes, Framer combines design and interactivity seamlessly, making it great for advanced animations and user interactions.\n\n9. **Marvel App**: Offers a simple interface for wireframing and prototyping. It includes features for user testing and design handoff.\n\nChoosing the best tool will depend on your specific use case, team collaboration needs, and personal preference. Many of these tools offer free trials, so it's a good idea to experiment with a few to determine which one works best for you.",
